Install multipass for launching machines locally:
1. multipass launch 22.04 -n primary -c 2 -m 4G -d 50G --name finityOne-test1
2. multipass launch 22.04 -n primary -c 2 -m 4G -d 50G --name finityOne-test2

Connect instances:
multipass shell finityOnetest-1
multipass shell finityOnetest-2

Script to install prerequisites: packages.sh

Default versions as inputs:
Docker: 27.2.0
Nginx: 1.18.0
PHP: 4.2.22
Postgre: 14.13
Redis: 7.2.5

#Docker
#Locate Dockerfile and index.html under the same folder
#Build Image
docker build -t my-nginx-site .
#Run container
sudo docker run -d -p 8081:80 -v index.html:/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html my-nginx-site

#Deploy Nginx (master and node)
1. Copy the nginx  to /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/default
2. Validate nginx
3. Retstart nginx - systemctl restart nginx


#POSTGRE Installation on node instance
1. Copy dockerfile to the node instance
2. sudo docker build -t my_nginx_postgres .
3. docker run -d -p 8081:80 -p 5432:5432 -v /var/run/postgresql:/tmp --user root --name postgres my_nginx_postgres


Next tasks:
1. Enable docker connectivity between master and node instances. 
When I send http://<MASTER-IP>/info-node.php I will get the php info of the node instance
in the docker container running there

2. Install postgress on the node instance inside the docker, and be able to send request
from the master instance to the postgress container running on the node instance.

3. Install Redis on the node instance.